<br>
We had a group of 5 heading to Disco which included a cleric, mage, wizard, chanter and myself as a monk. <br>
<br>
Just inside the door we killed a frog which dropped an Obulus Death Shroud.  I knew something had dropped but as I was fighting I missed what it was until the end.  The numbers were called to roll and while the others rolled I scrolled back up to see what had dropped.  I then rolled and won.  As it had taken 10-15 seconds from when I had rolled towhen others had finished it was assumed the chanter won and item was handed to him.  I had actually beaten him and instead of handing the item over he him and wizzie disbanded.  <br>
<br>
The wizard TL'ed the chanter to the Nexus and the ported herself there also. <br>
<br>
The remaining members of the group allpetitioned but as this occured around 4am PST there wasn't any GM's on to answer the petitions.  When I finished 6 hrs later my petition still hadn't been answered but as it was 3am my time it was time to leave. <br>
<br>
The enchanter actually confessed to the ninja-looting to the mage who promptly sent in a report of the confession to go along with petition.  <br>
<br>
At this stage I am unsure of what will happen to anyone or if I will be awarded the Shroud but that's not the important thing.  The point is these people stole something that they didn't win and should have turned it to the person who won it whether it be me or anyone else. <br>
<br>
The name of the enchanter is Jahsmite and the wizard was Angelical.  I don't think the chanter was guilded and I am also unsure of the wizard.  <br>
<br>
I know they are going on a few blacklists and just thought I would let you all know what these people do.  The shroud goes for 15-20k atm in the bazaar so it was obviously a greed loot, and I probably would sell it myself if I had it.  The point is I didn't take it from someone who had earned it. <br>
<br>
It is up to you whether you trust these people in the future but they won't be getting any hand-outs from me. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
